Thanks, love the inlining of `GetSigOpCount` (bothered me, too - it's a lot clearer this way), and the new `CountSigOps` name as well.
Added your comments (+ you as co-author, of course) and adjusted all the tests, now that `CountSigOps` is separated from `CountP2SHSigOps`: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/compare/6bf4c8d48f61089254532b065d9ca8e1c2bf6868..f8208e92bd103359f8c3ceb3361eb7904099e994

Edit: note, that instead of
```patch
-        sigops += prev_txo.scriptPubKey.GetSigOpCount(txin.scriptSig);
+        sigops += prev_txo.scriptPubKey.CountSigOps(/*fAccurate=*/true);
+        if (prev_txo.scriptPubKey.IsPayToScriptHash()) {
+           sigops += CountP2SHSigOps(txin.scriptSig);
+        }
```
I did:
```patch
-        sigops += prev_txo.scriptPubKey.GetSigOpCount(txin.scriptSig);
+        sigops += prev_txo.scriptPubKey.IsPayToScriptHash() ?
+                      CountP2SHSigOps(txin.scriptSig) :
+                      prev_txo.scriptPubKey.CountSigOps(/*fAccurate=*/true);
```

since I don't think `CountSigOps` should always be applied (even if always `0`)

